-- Housing Development, Suzlon: India Equity Preview (Correct)
-- Anoop Agrawal
-- 2010-07-13T03:02:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/housing-development-pfizer-suzlon-power-finance-india-equity-preview.html

          
          
             (Corrects third paragraph to show that Housing Development
Finance is India’s biggest mortgage lender.)  
 The following companies may have
unusual price changes in India trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  
 The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex,
advanced 103.66, or 0.6 percent, to 17,937.20. The S&P CNX Nifty
Index on the National Stock Exchange rose 0.6 percent to 5,383.
The BSE 200 Index rose 0.4 percent to 2,278.45.  
 Housing Development Finance Corp. (HDFC IN): The nation’s
biggest mortgage lender sold 2.25 billion rupees ($48 million)
of two-year zero-coupon notes, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg. The shares rose 2.3 percent to 2,049.45 rupees.  
 Pfizer Ltd. (PFIZ IN): The Indian unit of the world’s
biggest drugmaker said second-quarter profit rose to 345.9
million rupees from 312.9 million rupees a year earlier. The
shares fell 0.7 percent to 1,199.65 rupees.  
 Power Finance Corp. (POWF IN): The state-owned lender to
power projects plans to borrow $240 million, according to a
person familiar with the matter. The shares fell 0.9 percent to
304.85 rupees.  
 Suzlon Energy Ltd. (SUEL IN): The nation’s largest wind-
turbine maker won an order from the Malpani Group to set up,
operate and maintain two wind power plants that can generate
19.8 megawatts of power. The projects are in the states of
Maharashtra and Karnataka, Suzlon said yesterday in a statement
to the stock exchange. The shares rose 0.3 percent to 58.95
rupees.  
